variables : like boxes, containers that can hold some value
             1. dataType variableName = value; // int x = 10; [when we know the exact value to store]
             2. dataType variableName;         // int x;      [when we don't know the exact value to store]


    dataTypes:
       primitive data type
         where we know in advance how much memory they will consume
          Integer Numbers[byte, short, int, long] ==> int{if we have to do some mathematical operations]
          decimal Numbers[float, double] ==> up to 5-6 decimal places{float}, more than 6 decimal places{double}
          anything as single char [char]
          char n = '1'
          char m = '2'
          char sum =m+n;  // This won't follow mathematical rules instead will use Ascii rules
          true/false[boolean]

    non-primitive data type
        where we are unsure about memory consumption

    MathOperations:
        a) I/I = I part
           9/2 = 4

        b) D/I or I/D or D/D = I+D Part
           9.0/2 0r 9/2.0 or 9.0/2.0 = 4.5

        c) Mod Operator: This gives you the remainder
           9/2 = 1{Remainder}

        d) Increment Operator [i++, ++i]
           int x = 1;
           int y = x++;
           System.out.println(x);//2
           System.out.println(y);//1

           int x =1;
           int y = ++x;
           System.out.println(x)//2
           System.out.println(y)//2

        e) Decrement Operator
            int x = 1;
            int y = x--;
            System.out.println(x);//0
            System.out.println(y);//1

            int x =1;
            int y = --x;
            System.out.println(x)//0
            System.out.println(y)//0


    Statements: [To make Decisions]
        if-else Statement             [when we have to make single decision]
        multiple if else if statement [when we have to make condition based multiple decisions]
        switch statement               [when we have to make condition based multiple decisions] - Faster
          switch will not support: >, <, >=, <=, long, float, double, boolean, &&
          This means, use switch only if you have to make decision over the exact value


    Loops: [Repeat tasks]
        while loop
        [if we know the starting and ending point of program]
        [we can also use it if we are unsure about in how many iterations, end point will be achieved]

        variable
        while(applyConditionOverVariable)
        {
          code here will execute only if condition is true;
          I/D operator;
        }


        for loop
        [if we know the starting and ending point of program]

        for(variable;applyConditionOverVariable;I/D operator)
        {
           code here will execute only if condition is true
        }


        advanced for loop [over groups] [you can use this only if you have to traverse over all the values in a group]

        for(dataTypeOfGroup aliasName :nameOfTheGroup)
        {
           perform action over aliasValue;
        }


    Arrays: Boxes with multiple sections that can hold multiple value at a time
            1. dataType[] arrayName = {value1, value2, value3, value4........};
               [when we know the exact values to store]
               int[] marks = {12,14,56,78,56};

            2. dataType[] arrayName = new dataType[countOfValuesYouWantToStore]
               [when we don't know the exact values to store but know there count]
               WAP to store the marks of 10 students
               int[] marks = new int[10]

            Lowest index = 0
            Highest Index = size-1
            naming of every section
            arrayName[lowestIndex]......................................arrayName[highestIndex]
            marks[0].......................................marks[9]

    Class : A Template [which ideally doesn't hold any data]
    Object: Every copy of the template is known as its object
    Relationship b/w class & Object OR Syntax to create Object
    NameOfTheClassWhoseCopyYouWantTOCreate nameOfCopy/Object= new NameOfTheClassWhoseCopy/ObjectWeWantTOcreate();
    Ex: Automobile
    Automobile taxi = new Automobile();


    Methods:
    Layman's Definition: Reason for storing any variable or array is method
                         Or the purpose why you store something, the purpose itself is method.

    Technical Definition: Methods are actions performed over class variables

    accessModifier returnType methodName(can/t parameters)
    {
      action to perform
    }

   accessModifier : public/private/protected
                    public - if we want to share that method with other classes
                    private- if we don't want to share with other classes
                    protected - if we want to share with classes related to me

   returnType:      void/dataTypes
   parameters:     variables within the curved bracket


   method Without Parameter() Without Return Type[void]
   method With Parameter(something) Without Return Type[void]
   method Without Parameter() With Return Type [dataType]
   method With Parameter(something) With Return Type [dataType]

